OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Thu 4 Jun to Sat 13 Jun
OL,6,FAtlantic low pressure systems will
OL,7,Fcontinue to push showers or longer
OL,8,Fspells of rain east across the UK. The
OL,9,Fbest of the drier conditions are
OL,10,Fusually more likely towards the south
OL,11,Fand east, with more frequent rain
OL,12,Facross the west and northwest. Drier
OL,13,Fweather may start to become more
OL,14,Fdominant through the second week of
OL,15,FJune. Temperatures will be near-normal
OL,16,Foverall, with the warmest spots most
OL,17,Flikely across eastern areas. It will
OL,18,Falso be breezy at times, especially
OL,19,Facross western parts, and notably so
OL,20,Faround some coastal areas.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
